{
  "texts": [
    "Similarly, LLM categorization measures the innovation type by distinguishing between code development (which introduces new functionality) and maintenance (which enhances existing components).",
    "Our first approach identifies capability innovation by examining code diffs to determine when new functions are introduced.",
    "We analyze all code changes in each commit by processing the difference between previous and current versions of files modified in that commit.",
    "foot_3 Then, we count the number of functions added minus functions removed across all files in a commit.",
    "It's important to note that when an existing function is edited, it appears in code diffs as one function removed, and one function added."
  ]
}